The recommender system made unsuitable recommendation. 
 Its reasons are as follows: Extracted preferences/dislikes: I prioritize album-oriented, cohesive sequencing and records that reward full-playback listening; I like clear, present mixes and concise (3–5 minute) tracks with immediacy and punch (commanding vocals, drums/bass drive, riff/energy-forward production). I also value vocal-forward, warm mastering and reinterpretations when they present distinct takes. I dislike single-artist greatest‑hits compilations and other singles-driven, patched collections that undermine album-level cohesion, and I avoid releases that feel like a grab‑bag of eras rather than a unified listening experience.
