- The Very Best of Chicago: Only the Beginning — This is explicitly a horn‑driven anthology with warm analogue midrange, close but midrange lead vocals, tasteful organ/piano, restrained guitars, and low‑compression mastering that preserves dynamics and subtle instrumental detail. It is described as tightly sequenced for melodic, start‑to‑finish listening and vocal‑forward clarity. Those attributes map directly onto my stated gravitation toward well‑curated career anthologies, era/sequence sensitivity, warm vocal‑forward mastering, and preference for preserved dynamics rather than heavy compression or gimmicky vocal processing.
